            <div n="a" subtype="fragment" type="textpart">
               <p>
                  <milestone n="1" unit="line"/> [NN to Kleon, greetings.] I have sent you [a copy of the letter which Thra]syllos [has written to us]. 
<milestone n="5" unit="line"/> The sluice gate has to be opened so that the land in Theogenis may be irrigated as quickly as possible. Farewell. <milestone n="8" rend="break" unit="line"/> Thrasyllos to [NN], greetings. 
               </p>
            </div>
            <div n="b+c" subtype="fragment" type="textpart">
               <p>
                  <milestone n="9" unit="line"/> [...]. Because the water from the great canal coming from the locks in Ptolemais flows through slowly, 
I have diverted it to the desert canal [...]. <milestone n="13" unit="line"/> In the great canal the [...] beneath two/by two [...] 
in Ptolemais has been opened and what is now flowing through, is not sufficient for me. <milestone n="17" unit="line"/> Please, write immediately to Kleon to [...].
<note>Translation: B. Van Beek in P.Petr.Kleon, p. 79, © Peeters</note>
               </p>
            </div>
         </div>
      </body>
